fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static Non Reflective

data.description: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static Non-Reflective was released a day after its much more exclusive and limited Reflective sibling, so don't stress, if you weren't able to cop that release, this one is garnished with all the same trimmings, only minus the 3M reflective stripe. The Yeezy 350 Static both this one and the reflective are unlike any previous release we have seen, and it is becoming more and more evident that although existing in direct competition with one another, both Kanye West's Yeezy and Virgil Abloh's Off-White ranges, might quite possibly be cross-pollinating. Be ready for 2019, because it's only getting better with the Yeezy Static Non Reflective.

Whether you are a critic or a fan, there is no debating that the inaugural colourway for the Yeezy 700 Wave Runner, first released in November 2017 has set a new trend in the trainer world. Nicknamed the ‘Yeezy Wave Runner' this release pays homage to retro 90's stylings moving away from the minimalist silhouettes of previous Yeezys and opting to make a bolder and brasher statement. Promising re-energising comfort with every step, as well as developing a unique new style for anyone who wears it, the Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner is a clear statement that Kanye West is forever ahead of the curve with his releases, and continuously going against the status quo in the footwear scene.

The integrated lacing system means for a tailored fit, the Boost midsole offers comfort and the translucent rubber outsole provides grip. Complete with padding in its collar for added cushioning, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage is available to buy and sell with Laced.

Kanye West and Adidas strike again, bringing back the insanely popular 350 V2 in the classic Yeezy Israfil colourway. This colourway is very much on-brand for Yeezy's favourite colour combos, mixing plenty of natural hues. The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil sees a broad mix of greys interlaced within the famous primeknit upper— comfort guaranteed with this silhouette due to the use of this superb fabric. The signature Yeezy stripe, of course, features in a bold rust colour. Award-winning ultraboost technology can be found at the bottom of the Yeezy 350 Israfil. The ultraboost is housed within a grey/blue translucent midsole. As with all Yeezy's, the branding is minimal. The Adidas x Yeezy logo is featuring inside of the shoe. After a brief hiatus from releasing sneakers, we guarantee the Adidas Yeezy Boost Israfil will be an instant classic. Be sure to grab a pair to improve your sneaker rotation this summer.
Buy the Yeezy 700 MNVN Triple Black brand-new from Laced. Available in multiple sizes.

Boasting a versatile colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon presents an updated take on Kanye’s OG silhouette. The patchwork Primeknit upper is complete with a see-through mesh stripe which allows for extra ventilation. Underfoot, Boost cushioning offers comfort and the textured rubber outsole provides grip. Its integrated lacing system means for a tailored fit, while padding in the collar delivers support for your ankle. Buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon with Laced.

Presenting an all-new colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Stone is a versatile pair that will complement any everyday outfits. Its patchwork-style Primeknit upper is complete with a sidewall stripe detail and an integrated lacing system. Underfoot, Boost cushioning offers comfort and the semi-translucent outsole provides effective grip. Padding in the collar adds extra support, while the sock-like collar allows for a tailored fit. Find your size with Laced.

Originally only released in Asia, Africa and the Middle East, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth Reflective is defined by its neutral colourway and reflective detailing. Its Primeknit upper features a mesh stripe which allows for ventilation. Boost cushioning underfoot offers comfort, the semi-translucent rubber outsole provides grip and the integrated lacing system means for a secure fit. Finished with minimal branding, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth Reflective is available to buy and sell with Laced.

In-keeping with the brand's minimalistic aesthetic, the Yeezy Boost 700 V3 Safflower elevates the original Wave Runner with a futuristic design. Crafted with flexible Primeknit, a white cage surrounds the upper, while the supportive sock houses the functional lacing system. Rounded off with cushioning underfoot, the Yeezy Boost 700 V3 Safflower is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream Triple White

data.description: Boasting a neutral monochrome colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream Triple White presents an updated take on the classic 350 silhouette. Its breathable Primeknit upper is complete with an integrated lacing system and a pull tab at the heel. Underfoot, the Boost midsole offers comfort and the semi-translucent rubber outsole provides grip. Finished with padding in the collar for extra cushioning, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream Triple White is available to buy and sell with Laced.

Unique in both style and shape and staying true to Kanye West’s creative vision, the Yeezy 450 Utility Black is a must-have for any Yeezy fan. Following the success of the Dark Slate colourway comes this sleek all-black offering. A Primeknit sock-like construction guarantees a secure fit, whilst an EVA foam sole ensures comfort with every wear. A breathable mesh upper provides airflow to the foot, whilst a wave-like tread pattern provides all-season grip. A one-of-a-kind silhouette serving both function and fashion: add the Yeezy Boost 450 Utility Black to your rotation.

Yeezy 350 Cinder Painted in a dark charcoal, which is starkly different to the previously suggested black finish. The Yeezy Boost 350 v2 Cinder is perfect for those who love a darker trainer, but would prefer something slightly less conventional. With a single mesh stripe that shoots across the lateral panel, and a heroic return for the much loved, and missed pull hell tab, the Yeezy Cinder looks set to reach the heights achieved by some of the silhouettes premier models. The Yeezy 350 V2 Cinder is finished with a gum rubber out-sole that completes the shoe with a vivid yellow heel pod that finalises the versatile aesthetic, creating an addition to the Yeezy portfolio that can be styled in a multitude of ways.

Presenting an updated take on the OG 350 silhouette, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat is a streamlined everyday staple. Its Primeknit upper takes on a multi-coloured marbled pattern and is complete with a see-through mesh stripe. Boost cushioning underfoot offers comfort, the rubber outsole provides grip and a handle at the heel allows for an easy on and off. Fastened with an integrated lacing system, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat is available to buy and sell with Laced.

The second Yeezy 500 colourway released during NBA’s All-Star Weekend in 2018, the Yeezy 500 Blush stays true to Kanye West’s minimalistic vision. Dubbed the “Desert Rat”, supple suede and mesh dress the upper, complemented by a tonal chunky midsole. Fitted with functional laces, advanced cushioning underfoot and subtle hits of branding, shop the Yeezy 500 with Laced.

Introducing the Yeezy Foam Runner MX Carbon, a unique pair that offers an avant-garde silhouette as well as a comfortable fit. The MX Carbon adds even more energy to the one-of-a-kind silhouette, featuring Jackson Pollock-esque splashes of purple, grey, and yellow. It’s a sneaker style that will turn many heads, and the superior cushioning in the footbed will ensure they become a sneaker staple in your wardrobe. Also, as the shoes are partially constructed from recycled foam, it's a stylish way to develop a more sustainable wardrobe.

Boasting a two-tone design with neutral hues, the Yeezy 500 Clay Brown is an every-season staple. Utilising a branding-free upper crafted from suede and mesh, it’s reinforced by a rubber mudguard below. Putting comfort at the forefront of the design, the supportive adiPrene+ midsole is modelled on the ‘Feet You Wear’ technology used on Kobe Bryant’s KB8 3 from 1999. Buy and sell the Yeezy 500 Clay Brown with Laced.

Imbued with Ye’s futuristic aesthetic, the Yeezy 700 V3 Copper Fade is one of those sneakers you never knew you needed. Endlessly wearable and ideal for any occasion, this sneaker utilises modern design techniques, new-school technology and unique patterning to deliver a kick that you’ll want to wear every day. The upper is crafted from a breathable knitted mesh, while a durable caged overlay works to keep your foot firmly in place. A secure lace-up fastening puts you in control of the fit, while industry-leading cushioning is added to the midsole to keep you comfy all day long. Easy to style thanks to the clean copper and black colourway, the Yeezy 700 V3 Copper Fade deserves a place in your collection.

Refreshing the updated 350 model, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Jade Ash boasts an all-new two-toned colourway. The breathable Primeknit upper is decorated with a black stripe that features minimal branding. Underfoot, the Boost midsole offers comfort and the rubber outsole provides grip. Internal padding delivers extra cushioning and the integrated lacing system puts you in control of the fit. Complete with a sock-like collar, buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Jade Ash with Laced.

The brand new, for September 2019, Yeezy Cloud White colourway for the latest variant on the Yeezy Boost 350 v2 silhouette features a Primeknit bootie constructed which has become a staple of the models' icon status. With its now-signature semi-translucent side stripes and newest monicker, a heel pull tabless look. Full-length Boost technology is naturally encased in a tubular rubber sole unit on the Yeezy 350 Cloud White. While all this is emphasised by its combination pastel blue, white upper that lives up to the Yeezy Cloud White nickname.

In-keeping with the brand’s minimalistic style, the Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Cream is an effortless everyday staple. Rolled knit dresses the upper, while neutral nubuck overlays run across the sidewall, toe box and eyestays. Underfoot, the rubber outsole uses a classic herringbone traction pattern for optimised grip. Shop the Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Cream with Laced.

Ye is bringing back the Yeezy 700 v3 for a colourway fit for the summer. This will be the third rendition of the Yeezy 700 v3 we've been treated to, in the boldest colourway yet. The 700 v3 is Kanye's most daring design with Adidas, featuring a far sleeker sole than the armoured style we have become accustomed too. The upper also features webbing that we have rarely seen used before. The uppers remain in primeknit for optimum comfort as is expected, and comes in a mix of blues with various patterns interweaved. As mentioned above the 700 v3 breaks the boundaries of ordinary design, with the webbing being a translucent blue tint cage that also happens to glow in the dark. The futuristic aesthetic of this sneaker will have sneakerheads around the globe, wanting to cop a pair. If you are looking for a shoe that will help you stand out amongst the crowd, then the Arzareth is the answer.

Sporting Kanye West’s signature futuristic style, the Yeezy Boost 700 V3 Mono Safflower is an elevated take on adidas x Yeezy’s original Boost 700 design. With the same streamlined shape, the knitted upper is fitted with a durable cage that contours to your foot for customised support. The thick midsole is fitted with Boost cushioning for enhanced comfort, while the partially concealed lace-up fastening puts you in control of the fit. Easy to style thanks to its neutral and light yellow hues, the Yeezy Boost 700 V3 Mono Safflower is a must-have addition to your collection.

Sporting a cool-toned grey colourway, the Yeezy 450 Stone Teal refreshes the modern model that was first seen in 2021. Featuring minimal branding in true Yeezy style, the model’s unique resin sole unit wraps around its breathable Primeknit upper. A secure lacing system allows for a tailored fit, while the sock-like collar creates a streamlined silhouette. Utilising advanced fabrics and industry-leading comfort technology, shop the Yeezy 450 Stone Teal with Laced now.

Taking inspiration from previous Yeezy iterations, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Tail Light presents an updated take on the classic 350 silhouette. Its Primeknit upper is complete with a contrasting pull tab and a see-through mesh panel. The integrated lacing system puts you in control of the fit, Boost cushioning in the midsole offers comfort and the rubber outsole provides grip. Finished with padding in the collar for extra support, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Tail Light is available to buy and sell with Laced.

The newly released Yeezy 500 Ash Grey looks to further expand Kanye West's impressive portfolio of colourways for his signature chunky shape, this time dressing his popular 500 silhouettes in a mixed composition of Ash Grey. The familiar fusion of mesh fabric with suede overlays combines alongside the signature geometric cut-outs to complete the upper's unique design. Although theoretically monotonal, a more complex aesthetic is created on this trainer thanks to how each colour looks dependent on the material it is applied to. Beneath, a light grey mudguard with a slight green tint adds a slight contrast to the design, while the exaggerated sole of the Yeezy 500 Ash Grey is also present in a darker hue of ash grey to complete this latest entry to the Yeezy 500 catalogue.

Named after a constellation in the Southern Celestial Hemisphere the Yeezy Boost 350 v2 Antlia Non-Reflective is definitely out of the world. Dressed in an all over subtle golden yellow arriving on the v2 variation of possibly the trainer worlds most popular silhouette the Yeezy Boost 350, this model looks to expand an already extensive portfolio of excellent colourways further. This designs paint job is only offset by the gum hit found on the sole that wraps its way onto the toecap and heel which offers a classic finish to a very modern trainer. The difference between this new design and any of its predecessors is its lack of heel pull tab which sets this model apart as the only in the range to date of which to lack this feature.

A shoe that divided the internet upon its release, the adidas Yeezy Foam Runner was first spotted on the feet of Ye’s daughter North West back in 2019. Fast forward and the silhouette has since seen colourway after colourway snapped up by fans across the globe, and next in line is the Yeezy Foam Runner Vermilion. Reminiscent of the Yeezy 700 style, the streamlined silhouette is crafted for performance and pure levels of comfort. Nodding to West’s penchant for sustainability, it’s crafted entirely from EVA Foam which effortlessly wraps around your foot in a cage-like fit. Underfoot, the textured tread delivers optimised grip while cut-out panels provide air flow and breathability, making the Yeezy Foam Runner Vermilion a must-have for any collection.

Dressed in a monochrome colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Cinder presents an updated take on the iconic 350 model. A breathable mesh overlay sits atop a web-like design underneath and is complete with a pull at its heel. The secure lacing system allows for a tailored fit and padding in the collar offers added support. Underfoot, the Boost-cushioned midsole delivers comfort and the textured rubber outsole provides grip. Buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Cinder with Laced.

The must-have design from the Kanye West range of Yeezys returns, this time with an attractive stone-white running throughout for a minimalistic colourway you can wear time and again. The Yeezy Foam Runner Stone Sage gives off a rather sporty look, perfect for the streets or for a comfortable slider during your downtime. The foam construction of the shoe guarantees the comfort and moulding capabilities you’ve come to expect from a pair of Yeezys, and the light stone colour offers a refreshing look. Throughout the slider, you have large perforations running from toe to heel, meaning maximum breathability and comfort with every step. Chunky midsole detailing and a tractioned outer sole means boosted comfort and a supported step. The Yeezy Foam Runner Stone Sage model is then complete with grooves running along the outer sole.

No pair of Yeezys would be complete without an iconic block colour choice, and here, we have this pair of sliders in a neon glow green set to turn heads and add a burst of colour to any outfit. The Yeezy Slide Glow Green remains true to the unconventional and unique design choice that all fans love. Keeping its sleek rubber upper and corrugated sole design, this shoe bumps up block colour to the max with a fully saturated neon green offering. With lightweight comfort always in mind, this pair of Yeezy Slide Glow Green is durable and flexible for a comfortable fit every time. The ease of these sliders is emphasised by the quick slip-on and off design. The grooves of the sole provide added traction and grip for easy wear.

The popular Yeezy Linen was released as part of Kanye Wests Spring Summer 2020 Collection. The Yeezy 350 Linen v2 looks to be a design evolved from the previously released 'Antlia' colourway that dropped in 2019. Painted in a clean beige hue which most peoples colour palette would acknowledge as being more yellowish than anything. Across the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Linen's iconic upper, a mesh stripe shoots across the lateral side panels. A now traditional motif signature on all the more recent additions to the Yeezy 350 portfolio. Accompanying this again, a brand standard set of fit laces offer the only purely functional feature on the design. Contrasting the subtle beige/yellow hue that imprints the Yeezy Linen's upper and midsole, in injections of baby blue that are presented on the sockliner and aforementioned mesh stripe. While further complement is paid to the design via a rose pink outsole that lines the bottom of the patented Adidas Boost unit. This pastel imaginary is perfect for Spring and Summer, hopefully capturing imaginations, improving outfits everywhere.

This pair of Yeezy 450 Cinders comes with a truly unique look for those lovers of something a little different (as well as fans of Kanye West’s striking aesthetic). This pair of Yeezy 450 Cinder's offers a different look to the classic slider, with a fully covered sock-like fabric finish on top for a light and easy wear, here in a light golden brown hue with matching laces and fabric collar detailing. The fabric sock offers maximum breathability as well as a comfortable fit and easy pull-on pull-off wear. For the rubber sole, you have an almost claw-like grip along the bottom and sides in a light brown hue that moves to deeper brown towards the back. This supportive sole offers maximum comfort for your step as well as traction and the boost you can expect from a pair of Yeezys.

A futuristic follow-up to the crowd-favourite Yeezy 350, the Yeezy Boost 380 Calcite Glow takes on a pared-back design. Dressed with flexible Primeknit, the upper hosts breathable perforations, glow-in-the-dark details and a sock-like fit. Finished with a secure lace-up fastening, the Yeezy Boost 380 Calcite Glow is available to buy and sell with Laced.

A technically advanced sneaker first seen in 2020, the Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown puts comfort at the forefront of the design. Crafted with flexible Primeknit, the upper features brown underlays, supportive caging and a functional lacing system. Underfoot, encased cushioning delivers all-day comfort, complete with textured tread for grip. An everyday essential, shop the Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown with Laced.

A vibrant take on the original Wave Runner, the adidas Yeezy 700 Wash Orange is an industry-defining silhouette from 2021. With a streamlined silhouette, the Primeknit upper provides flexibility, while a functional lacing system offers support. Boost cushioning is added underfoot, while a textured tread rounds off the design. Buy and sell the adidas Yeezy 700 Wash Orange with Laced.

With a two-tone colourway in neutral tones, the Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper elevates the classic silhouette. Flexible Primeknit dresses the upper, while the translucent sole houses Boost technology. Featuring breathable perforations, rope-like laces and a supportive collar, buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper with Laced.

The Yeezy 450 is one of Kanye West's most daring designs to come out of his collaboration with adidas. First teased back in 2018, this intricate design has since been released in Cloud White and now in the sleek Dark Slate 450 iteration. The shoe's base is crafted from a faded black Primeknit material, making the sneaker both lightweight and extremely comfortable. Chunky rope laces weave throughout the sock-like upper whilst the upper runs further up the ankle than your usual sneaker. The real showstopper with the 450 is its unique sole unit, as the futuristic wave-like pattern runs up both lateral and medial sides of the sneaker. The sole unit also features in the Dark Slate hue, giving the eye-catching Yeezy 450 Dark Slate a stealthy appearance to go alongside its modern aesthetics.

Pulled straight from Kanye West's 'Special Release' collection and made available exclusively in Europe the Yeezy 350 V2 Trueform proves that the Yeezy production line looks in no way like its slowing down. Channelling elements of both the Static and the highly coveted Beluga colourways the Trueform boasts a greyed out Primeknit upper and sits on top of a Boost midsole which fades from a dark grey at the top to a vibrant orange at the bottom. The updated Yeezy Boost V2 silhouette remains, building off the success of the Static in late December 2018 with the translucent stripe shooting down the laterals once again takes centre stage, allowing wearers to flex their socks while donning these kicks. The Trueform despite its limited continent release has worldwide appeal, and you should think yourself very lucky if you get your hands on a pair.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cmpct Slate Bone

data.description: Part of the Yeezy x adidas Autumn/Winter 2022 collection, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Bone takes cues from the original 350 design, elevating it with modern references. The traditional Primeknit upper remains, enhanced with a textured pattern and breathable gaps, but what really sets this sneaker apart is the sock-like collar and toggle-fastened laces, offering a close fit that flexes with the natural movement of your foot. The midsole is fitted with industry-leading Boost cushioning, while the specially shaped midsole offers suspension and traction. Easy to style thanks to the grey Slate colourway, add the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Bone to your collection now.

Experimental and bold: meet the Yeezy Boost 700 Hi-Res Red, a playful take on a well-loved style. Layered with various contrasting materials including soft suede pieces on the toe and bright leather eyestay panels, this sneaker holds hits of teal and orange, complemented by muted tones. With trademark full-length Boost cushioning within the textured midsole and padding within the collar, this stand-out pair delivers ultimate comfort for those who want to make a statement everyday. Complete with Three-Stripe branding on the shoe’s sidewall, the Yeezy Boost 700 Hi-Res Red is a vibrant celebration of all things Yeezy, with different coloured accents working together to highlight the complex shape of this popular model.

Dressed in a neutral colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Natural presents an updated take on the OG 350 silhouette. Its two-toned Primeknit upper is complete with an integrated lacing system and a see-through mesh stripe. Underfoot, the Boost midsole offers comfort and the semi-translucent rubber outsole provides grip. Finished with padding in the collar for extra cushioning, buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Natural with Laced.

If you’re a fan of Kanye West’s footwear line, then you can’t go wrong with a standout pair of Yeezys, built for unique design and maximum comfort. This pair of Yeezy Foam Mist Runners comes with a premium upper and a light brown hue running throughout. The streamlined and curved design means maximum comfort with every step, while the large perforation detailing means absolute breathability with every wear. The rubber outer sole blends in with the light brown upper perfectly in a matching hue, making the Yeezy Foam Runner Mist a runner that combines style with functionality that every wardrobe needs, no matter the season. The slip-on style also makes this shoe perfect for easy wear and for those with a life on the go.

Straying from Yeezy's typical minimalistic style, the Yeezy Boost 700 Enflame Amber is a technically advanced sneaker with a vibrant colourway. Drawing inspiration from the original Wave Runner, the chunky silhouette is crafted from suede and mesh, while the rubber sole houses Boost cushioning. Complete with a secure lace-up fastening, shop the Yeezy Boost 700 Enflame Amber with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Mx Sand Grey

data.description: A shoe that divided opinions when it first hit the sneaker scene, the Yeezy Foam Runner is proof of Kanye West’s creativity and innovation. This updated iteration, the Yeezy Foam Runner MX Sand Grey, takes Ye’s typically neutral colour scheme and brightens it with eye-catching hits of pink and grey. Its sporty silhouette remains unchanged, complete with caged-effect perforations running along the length of the shoe for the ultimate breathability. Easy to slip on and off, the lightweight rubber fabric makes it a comfortable choice for all-day wear. The upper of the Yeezy Foam Runner MX Sand Grey Pink is finished with a series of ridges that will be familiar to any Yeezy fan.

If you have been wanting to pick up a pair of Yeezy's but were awaiting a far brighter colourway than the usual earthy tones we are used to seeing, then your wait is over. The Yeezy Boost 700 Sun is one of the boldest colourways we have seen of the iconic silhouette, a must-cop for summer. The legendary wave runner design features across the shoe's toe box, whilst the rest of the upper is dripping in a bright yellow hue. Underfoot, the usual sole unit features but again the colour is completely switched up, with a bright orange midsole dominating the look, a black outsole finalises the design of this 700. This sole unit houses the iconic Ultra Boost technology making this sneaker one of the most comfortable shoes to wear. Aptly dubbed the Sun due to this golden colourway, we expect this Yeezy Boost 700 to be the shoe of the summer.
